resources so that you

00:03:57.220 --> 00:04:00.500
can keep going in spite
of some kind of failure.

00:04:00.500 --> 00:04:02.710
In the last part,
there are not just

00:04:02.710 --> 00:04:05.930
these accidental or
natural kinds of failures,

00:04:05.930 --> 00:04:07.420
but there are
deliberate failures.

00:04:07.420 --> 00:04:08.560
There are attacks.

00:04:08.560 --> 00:04:10.870
And the question
then becomes, what

00:04:10.870 --> 00:04:13.960
does one do about
defending a process?

00:04:13.960 --> 00:04:15.940
How does one continue
to work, even

00:04:15.940 --> 00:04:19.899
in the presence of
deliberate attacks?

00:04:19.899 --> 00:04:22.300
